## `test_open_creat_on_existing_is_fine(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-open-7 -->

### Purpose
`O_CREAT` without `O_EXCL` on an existing file is not an error — it just opens the existing file (mode is not applied to the existing file).

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/a", mode=0o644)
as_root.write(fd, b"original", offset=0)
as_root.close_fd(fd)

fd = as_root.open("/a", flags=os.O_CREAT | os.O_RDONLY, mode=0o777)
# Content unchanged; mode unchanged.
assert as_root.read(fd, size=8, offset=0) == b"original"
as_root.close_fd(fd)
assert as_root.stat("/a").mode & 0o777 == 0o644
```

---

